 --Add commas to long numbers--<
 //Example of use is if you have a gwc.userdata etc. that is a large number, you just do formatNumber(gwc.userdata.example) in whatever you're appending or replacing etc.
 function formatNumber(num) {
 if (num == null) return "0";
 return Number(num).toLocaleString();
 }
 //Examples:
 gwc.output.append(formatNumber(1000));
 gwc.output.append(formatNumber(gwc.userdata.alltimeKills));
 //Explanation:
 //Formats numbers like 1000 → 1,000 to make them easier to read

